            . On the 17th of April I was at <placeName id="t18220417-223-crimeloc1175">Paddington</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220417-223-crimeloc1175" type="placeName" value="Paddington"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220417-223-crimeloc1175" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220417-223-off1173 t18220417-223-crimeloc1175"></join>, about twelve o'clock in the morning, and saw a gentleman's gig standing at a door, and saw the prisoner take a bundle out of the gig, and run off with it. I gave information; it was hat in a handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-223-person2004">
                  SIMON 
                  PURDUE
               <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2004" type="surname" value="PURDUE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2004" type="given" value="SIMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2004" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to 
               <persName id="t18220417-223-person2005">
                  Thomas 
                  Wood
               <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2005" type="surname" value="Wood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2005" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-223-person2005" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; the gig stood at No. 45, Paddington-street. I was in the house; I left a hat, tied in a handkerchief; I had not left it a moment before the alarm was given; I missed it, and pursued the man, but could not see him; I gave information at the office, and saw the handkerchief two days afterwards, but have never found the hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-223-person2006">
                  THOMAS 
                  POYLE
